.TH _getshort 3
.SH NAME
\*L_getshort\*O \- Retrieves short quantities from a byte stream
.SH LIBRARY
Standard C Library \*L(libc.a)
.SH SYNOPSIS 
.sS
\*L#include <sys/types.h>
.sp .4v
\*L#include <netinet/in.h>
.sp .4v
\*L#include <arpa/nameser.h>
.PP 
\*L#include <resolv.h>
.sp .4v
\*Lunsigned short getshort (
.sp .4v
	\*Lu_char *\*Vmessage_ptr \*L);
.sE 
.SH PARAMETERS
.\"from TP "  
.VL 
.LI "\*Vmessage_ptr"
\*OSpecifies
a pointer into the byte stream.
.LE 
.SH DESCRIPTION
.iX "_getshort function"
.iX "byte stream" "retrieving short quantities from"
.PP 
The \*L_getshort(\|)\*O function gets quantities from thebyte stream or arbitrary
byte boundaries.
.PP 
The \*L_getshort(\|)\*O function is one of a set of subroutines
that form the \*Oresolver, a set of functions
that resolve domain names.  Global information that is used by the
resolver functions is kept in the \*L_res\*O data structure.
The \*Linclude/resolv.h\*O
file contains
the \*L_res \*Odata structure definition.
.SH RETURN VALUES
.PP 
Upon successful completion,
the \*L_getshort(\|)\*O function returns an unsigned \*Oshort
\*O(16-bit) value.
.PP
